$

== Another one.

$(Omega, cal(F), P)$ with $S$ a semimartingale, $FF$ is the $P$-augmented filtration generated by $W$.  $dd(S_t) = mu_t dd(t) + sigma dd(W_t), mu_t$ is a continuous adapted process, $sigma > 0$.

Find $Q approx P$ on $cal(F)_T$ s.t. $S$ is a $Q$-local martingale. 

_Solution sketch_. $P$ is positive, hence the density process $Z_t = cal(E)(L)_t$ is a $P$-local martingale iff. $L$ is a $P$-local martingale. 

Take the martingale representation of $L$ under the $P$-augmented filtration wrt. BM $FF$: 
$
L_t = integral_0^dot alpha_s dd(W_s)_t, alpha in L^2_"loc" (W).
$

Use Girsanov: $W$ is a $P$-BM $=> W^Q_t = W_t - al L, W ar_t = W_t - integral_0^t alpha_s dd(s).$ 

$
  dd(S_t) = (mu_t + sigma alpha_t) dd(t) + sigma dd(W_t^Q).
$

Since $S_t$ is a $Q$-local martingale, $mu_t + sigma alpha_t = 0 => alpha_t = -mu_t / sigma => dd(S_t) = sigma dd(W_t^Q)$.